metadata.name: MOUNT FUJI
metadata.description:
Postage stamp featuring the Mount Fuji located on Honshu Island. It is the highest mountain in Japan at 3776.24 m. It is an active stratovolcano that last erupted in 1707-08. Mt. Fuji lies about 100 kms south-west of Tokyo and can be seen from there on a clear day. Cherry blossom trees are also very common in the country. Sound effects give the perfect Asian essence to this piece.

Nippon is a significant word in all Japanese stamps.
